The Unveiling Of The BBI Taskforce Recommendations At The Bomas Of Kenya To All Kenyans Seems To Have Landed A False Start If Political Differences Witnessed During The Five Hour Event Is Anything To Go By. Drama Started After Nairobi Governor Mike Sonko Protested Having Been Left Out Of The Programme, A Matter That Was Further Reinforced By Senate Majority Leader Kipchumba Murkomen Both Claiming Organizers Of The Event Had Deliberately Isolated Leaders Allied To The Deputy President Prompting Senator Yusuf Haji To Step In To Restore Normalcy. ANC Party Leader Musalia Mudavadi Had Equally Stated That What Is Ailing The Country Is The Failing Economy Which Must Be    Fixed And Not Politics Of Inclusivity.